![1, ten dollar bill. 1, five dollar bill. 3, one dollar bills.](https://cdn.kastatic.org/ka-perseus-images/f3ce00298a63960007554158d7a90819012dcf23.png)

$\begin{align}
&\underbrace{\$\goldE{10}}_{\goldE{1}{\text{ ten dollar bill}}}  
 + \underbrace{\$\purpleD{5}}_{\purpleD{1}{\text{ five dollar bill}}}   +\underbrace{\$\blueE{1}+\$\blueE{1} + \$\blueE{1}}_{\blueE{3}{\text{ one dollar bills}}}\\\\
&\underbrace{\$\goldE{10}}_{\goldE{1}{\text{ ten dollar bill}}}  
 + \underbrace{\$\purpleD{5}}_{\purpleD{1}{\text{ five dollar bill}}}   +\underbrace{\$\blueE{3}}_{\blueE{3}{\text{ one dollar bills}}}=\$18
\end{align}$

This set of bills has a value of $\$18$, so it is **not** equal to $\$80$.
